Senator Mark Udall supports President Obama's speech on debt reduction and the economy. He specifically agrees with ending tax cuts for millionaires and believes that investments in programs that promote economic growth and cutting ineffective programs are necessary. Udall also emphasizes the importance of addressing the national debt, encouraging private-sector job growth, and preserving the American dream. While he believes that the president's budget aligns with some recommendations from the Bowles-Simpson Deficit Commission, he calls for a more comprehensive approach that considers all options. Udall welcomes the president's leadership and urges leaders from both parties to work together in reducing debt and improving the economy.